    <!-- About Hero -->
    <section class="about-hero">
        <h1>About CrimeSpotter UK</h1>
        <p>Making UK crime data accessible and understandable for everyone</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="about-container">
        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p>
                CrimeSpotter UK is dedicated to providing transparent, accessible, and easy-to-understand crime data 
                for communities across the United Kingdom. We believe that informed citizens make safer communities, 
                and access to crime statistics is a fundamental right.
            </p>
            <p>
                By visualizing official police data on interactive maps and providing detailed analytics, we empower 
                residents, businesses, and local authorities to make informed decisions about safety and security.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>Data Source & Accuracy</h2>
            <p>
                All crime data displayed on CrimeSpotter UK comes directly from the official UK Police API, which 
                aggregates reported crimes from all 43 police forces across England, Wales, and Northern Ireland.
            </p>
            <p>
                The data is updated monthly, typically with a 2-month delay to allow for verification and processing. 
                For example, data for June would typically be available in August. We refresh our database as soon as 
                new data becomes available.
            </p>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>Key Features</h2>
            <div class="feature-grid">
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-map-marked-alt"></i></div>
                    <h3>Interactive Maps</h3>
                    <p>Explore crime data with our intuitive map interface</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-sync-alt"></i></div>
                    <h3>Real-time Updates</h3>
                    <p>Monthly data refreshes from official sources</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-filter"></i></div>
                    <h3>Advanced Filtering</h3>
                    <p>Filter by crime type, date, and location</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-chart-bar"></i></div>
                    <h3>Detailed Analytics</h3>
                    <p>Comprehensive statistics and trend analysis</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-mobile-alt"></i></div>
                    <h3>Mobile Friendly</h3>
                    <p>Access crime data on any device</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-item">
                    <div class="feature-icon"><i class="fas fa-lock"></i></div>
                    <h3>Privacy Focused</h3>
                    <p>No personal data collection or tracking</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="about-section">
            <h2>Privacy & Security</h2>
            <p>
                We take your privacy seriously. CrimeSpotter UK does not collect, store, or share any personal 
                information. We don't use cookies for tracking, and all map searches are processed anonymously.
            </p>
            <p>
                The crime data we display is already anonymized by the UK Police before publication. Exact locations 
                are approximated to protect the privacy of victims and maintain the integrity of ongoing investigations.
            </p>
        </section>


    </div>

